WEBVTT

00:01.160 --> 00:02.958
Previously on
"Life Sentence"...

00:03.000 --> 00:04.570
What is happening?
Is there an emergency?

00:04.630 --> 00:06.200
There's a new oncologist
on the floor, and he's...

00:06.250 --> 00:07.456
So hot.

00:07.500 --> 00:09.298
Hi.
Dr. William Grant.

00:09.340 --> 00:11.217
Stella Abbott, volunteer.

00:11.260 --> 00:13.422
Stella: I helped Lizzie
get into a writers' retreat

00:13.470 --> 00:14.835
so she could finally focus.

00:14.890 --> 00:16.927
You can do better
than selling ADHD meds

00:16.970 --> 00:18.881
to desperate
soccer moms.

00:18.930 --> 00:20.011
It's not like
I haven't thought about

00:20.060 --> 00:21.266
doing other things.

00:21.310 --> 00:22.596
We can't ignore this
anymore.

00:22.640 --> 00:24.347
I knew he sold weed
years ago.

00:24.400 --> 00:25.856
I didn't know
about the pills.

00:25.900 --> 00:28.767
Wes: When I bumped into you,
everything changed.

00:28.820 --> 00:30.857
Pippa: I flew to Paris
and went to that restaurant

00:30.900 --> 00:32.311
where we'd made
the reservation.

00:32.360 --> 00:33.566
Stella: You were there?
In Paris?

00:33.610 --> 00:34.907
Wes:
I was supposed to marry her.

00:34.950 --> 00:36.941
Five days
before I met you.

00:36.990 --> 00:38.731
How long have you
been married? Six months.

00:38.780 --> 00:40.748
It's a shame I didn't meet you
seven months ago.

00:40.790 --> 00:43.782
I'm not sticking this out
to fulfill a promise.

00:43.830 --> 00:45.241
I want to be here.
With you.

00:45.290 --> 00:47.031
I want to be here with you,
too.

00:49.670 --> 00:51.081
Stella: I'm really glad
we're doing this.

00:51.130 --> 00:53.087
We haven't seen a movie
in ages.

00:53.130 --> 00:55.007
Well, I thought
it would be a good idea

00:55.050 --> 00:56.290
to "Forget Paris"

00:56.340 --> 00:58.297
and take a little
"Roman Holiday."

00:59.810 --> 01:01.175
What's this movie about,
again?

01:01.220 --> 01:04.974
Audrey Hepburn rides
a tiny scooter around Rome.

01:05.019 --> 01:08.149
Ooh! Say no more.
I'm gonna love this.

01:09.020 --> 01:10.317
Wes: Ooh.

01:10.360 --> 01:12.180
I told you
if you wanted popcorn

01:12.230 --> 01:13.561
to get your own.

01:13.610 --> 01:15.021
The tub's bigger
than you are.

01:15.070 --> 01:19.735
And yet,
I shall consume it all.

01:21.830 --> 01:24.492
[ Man speaking indistinctly
on screen |

01:24.540 --> 01:25.826
Hey.

01:25.870 --> 01:28.282
Thank you for being
so understanding

01:28.330 --> 01:29.741
about the whole Pippa thing.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.372
I love you.

01:31.420 --> 01:33.252
I love you, too.

01:33.300 --> 01:35.086
I'd love for you
to be quiet.

01:35.130 --> 01:36.336
Sorry.

01:36.380 --> 01:37.791
We just went through
a really trying time

01:37.840 --> 01:39.046
in our relationship
SO -- Woman: Shh!

01:39.090 --> 01:41.309
Oh, uh, I'm sorry.
I had no idea.

01:41.350 --> 01:43.341
Maybe we should stop the movie,
turn on the lights,

01:43.390 --> 01:45.222
and you two
can act out your drama

01:45.270 --> 01:46.476
for the whole theater?

01:46.520 --> 01:47.510
Okay, relax.

01:47.560 --> 01:49.392
It's just the trailers...

01:49.440 --> 01:52.819
for movies that came out,
like, 60 years ago.

01:52.860 --> 01:55.238
Stella: Wes and I
weren't the only ones

01:55.280 --> 01:57.487
trying to reset
our relationship.

01:57.530 --> 01:59.692
"Only the chickens
and Henrietta's family

01:59.740 --> 02:01.447
knew the real answer."

02:01.490 --> 02:03.868
Now that she was home
from the writer's retreat,

02:03.910 --> 02:05.651
Lizzie and Diego were trying
to do the same thing.

02:05.700 --> 02:06.952
"...to save their hides.

02:07.000 --> 02:08.866
For even though
she was a chicken,

02:08.919 --> 02:10.490
she was family.

02:10.539 --> 02:11.951
Mama?
Yeah?

02:12.000 --> 02:14.549
Did you really write
that story? I did.

02:14.590 --> 02:16.627
Just for
the two of you guys

02:16.670 --> 02:18.798
because I missed you
so much.

02:18.840 --> 02:20.581
I'll read you another one
tomorrow, okay?

02:20.640 --> 02:23.007
But for now,
it's time for bed.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.630
Let's go.

02:28.560 --> 02:30.050
I'm gonna
put them to bed,

02:30.100 --> 02:31.397
and then I'm gonna
put you to bed.

02:31.440 --> 02:33.932
Okay.

02:34.730 --> 02:36.778
I am so happy
that you're finally home.

02:36.820 --> 02:38.640
I'm so happy to be home.
Oh, yeah?

02:38.700 --> 02:41.567
<i>Ooh.
Ooh! Wine!</i>

02:41.620 --> 02:42.860
Nice.

02:42.910 --> 02:44.730
Thank you guys
for letting me stay here

02:44.790 --> 02:48.249
because I am lonely.

02:48.290 --> 02:50.076
Breaking up
with your girlfriend

02:50.120 --> 02:51.827
who's also
your best friend...

02:51.880 --> 02:53.166
really sucks.

02:56.300 --> 02:57.256
Hmm.

02:58.380 --> 02:59.836
Oh, smells like dirt.

03:01.220 --> 03:03.257
So, let's Netflix and chill,
kids.

03:03.300 --> 03:04.426
Mom.
Yeah?

03:04.470 --> 03:05.710
Do you know
what that means?

03:05.760 --> 03:07.012
I do not.

03:08.640 --> 03:11.268
Aiden was trying to make
a fresh start, too.

03:11.310 --> 03:12.436
Aiden, all you have to do

03:12.480 --> 03:13.891
is finish filling out
this profile.

03:13.940 --> 03:15.396
Look.

03:15.440 --> 03:16.817
It's not that I don't want
to go legit, guys.

03:16.860 --> 03:18.396
I do, but the truth is,

03:18.440 --> 03:20.351
there's no reason anyone
would ever want to hire me.

03:20.400 --> 03:22.619
That's not true.
Really?

03:22.660 --> 03:25.027
That's exactly what the manager
at Better Buy said.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.445
Aiden, you're smart.

03:26.490 --> 03:27.616
And resourceful.

03:27.660 --> 03:28.900
If I was resourceful,

03:28.950 --> 03:30.406
would I still be
living with my father,

03:30.460 --> 03:31.825
letting him pay
all my bills?

03:31.870 --> 03:33.201
Yes.

03:33.250 --> 03:34.411
That's the definition
of resourceful.

03:34.460 --> 03:36.167
Guys, let's face it.

03:36.210 --> 03:37.792
I'm unemployable.

03:37.840 --> 03:39.160
You don't have a choice,
Aiden.

03:39.210 --> 03:41.042
You want to keep
living here for free,

03:41.090 --> 03:42.501
you have to get
a real job.

03:42.550 --> 03:43.836
Well, that's just great.

03:43.890 --> 03:45.676
I'm gonna take
that ultimatum,

03:45.720 --> 03:47.711
hop on my unicorn,
and ride on down

03:47.770 --> 03:49.886
to the Department
of Magical Thinking,

03:49.930 --> 03:52.729
where they hand out
government jobs building rainbows.

03:57.570 --> 03:58.640
That's not funny.

03:58.690 --> 04:00.317
Wasn't funny.

04:00.360 --> 04:02.692
Hey, guys,
I got no references,

04:02.740 --> 04:05.311
no job history,
and no experience.

04:05.370 --> 04:07.111
Who in the world's
ever gonna hire me?

04:09.290 --> 04:11.156
The coffee shop.

04:11.210 --> 04:12.609
Duh!

04:12.670 --> 04:14.206
I can't believe I didn't
think of this sooner.

04:14.250 --> 04:15.820
I had none of those things
either,

04:15.880 --> 04:17.620
and they still hired me.

04:17.670 --> 04:18.956
Plus, you're family,

04:19.000 --> 04:20.582
so that's got to count
for something.

04:20.630 --> 04:22.587
I find nepotism
repulsive.

04:22.630 --> 04:24.507
Doesn't your father
own this coffee shop?

04:24.550 --> 04:26.507
Yes, and he made me
interview for my job

04:26.550 --> 04:28.132
like I was
a complete stranger.

04:28.180 --> 04:30.638
Look.

04:30.680 --> 04:32.887
My brother
is a great guy.

04:32.940 --> 04:35.227
Is that him?
Yeah.

04:35.270 --> 04:36.476
And I'm telling you,

04:36.520 --> 04:37.476
he would make
the best barista.

04:37.520 --> 04:38.817
He's such a people person.

04:38.860 --> 04:40.931
He's good at smiling
and winking

04:40.990 --> 04:42.697
and handing people
things in cups.

04:42.740 --> 04:44.196
Just...stop.

04:44.240 --> 04:45.696
You had me at
how hot his face is.

04:45.740 --> 04:46.810
He can have the job.

04:46.870 --> 04:47.860
Oh, my God.

04:47.910 --> 04:49.696
Thank --
Oh! Not a hugger.

04:49.740 --> 04:52.710
Oh. I'm sorry.

04:52.750 --> 04:55.367
Finley,
meet my brother, Aiden.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.957
Aiden, meet Finley,
your new boss.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.207
Welcome aboard,
handsome.

05:00.250 --> 05:02.378
- That killer smile
is part of your uniform,

05:02.420 --> 05:05.082
and I expect you to wear it
to work every single day.

05:05.130 --> 05:07.212
Ooh. Anything you say,
boss lady.

05:07.260 --> 05:08.716
Oh.

05:08.760 --> 05:10.637
Hey, I don't have to wear
this stupid hat, do I?

05:10.680 --> 05:11.636
Oh. No.

05:11.680 --> 05:13.136
We just make Stella wear it

05:13.180 --> 05:14.636
because she's got such
an oddly shaped head.

05:15.730 --> 05:17.892
No, I don't.

05:17.940 --> 05:21.433
Finley's insults aside,
I was really killing it today,

05:21.480 --> 05:22.982
which probably
isn't a good thing to say

05:23.030 --> 05:24.236
at a hospital.

05:24.280 --> 05:25.850
Hey.

05:25.900 --> 05:27.402
How's it going,
"Mighty Mouse"?

05:27.450 --> 05:28.611
Mighty Mouse?

05:28.660 --> 05:29.730
Is that supposed to be
my nickname?

05:29.780 --> 05:30.861
When did
I get a nickname?

05:30.910 --> 05:31.729
Just now.

05:31.790 --> 05:33.076
Just gave it to you.

05:33.120 --> 05:34.827
Well, I'm great.
Really killing it today.

05:34.870 --> 05:37.077
Okay, that's not a good
thing to say at a hospital. Mm.

05:37.120 --> 05:38.918
Dr. Grant: But I am glad
that you're having a good day,

05:38.960 --> 05:40.450
and I think your day
is about to get better.

05:40.500 --> 05:42.377
I just found out
that Sadie got accepted

05:42.420 --> 05:44.081
into Dr. Friedman's
clinical trial.

05:44.130 --> 05:45.165
Are you serious?

05:46.180 --> 05:47.750
Oh, my God.

05:47.800 --> 05:49.382
That's amazing!

05:49.430 --> 05:50.716
Yeah.

05:56.810 --> 05:58.517
Oh, oh, oh, oh

05:58.560 --> 05:59.607
Oh, oh, oh, oh

05:59.650 --> 06:00.799
Oh, oh, oh, oh, ah, ah

06:00.860 --> 06:02.771
A little bit dangerous

06:02.820 --> 06:03.855
Oh, oh, oh, oh

06:03.900 --> 06:05.390
Oh, oh, oh, oh

06:05.440 --> 06:06.987
Oh, oh, oh, oh, ah, ah

06:07.030 --> 06:07.815
I'm a little bit dangerous
Oh, Stella.

06:07.860 --> 06:09.521
Stella.

06:09.570 --> 06:10.901
Dr. Grant: Stella.

06:10.950 --> 06:12.111
You okay?

06:12.160 --> 06:13.321
Hmm? Yeah.

06:13.370 --> 06:15.281
N

06:15.330 --> 06:19.119
You got a little drool here. Oh.

06:19.170 --> 06:20.569
I was afraid you were
having a stroke.

06:20.630 --> 06:22.587
Mnh-mnh.
No. I-I'm good.

06:22.630 --> 06:24.041
I'm great.

06:24.090 --> 06:25.956
I'm just having
a sexual fantasy

06:26.010 --> 06:28.297
about a man
who isn't my husband.

06:28.340 --> 06:31.549
Don't worry about a thing

06:31.600 --> 06:35.309
You'll learn to live again

06:35.350 --> 06:37.227
You're gonna learn
to live again

06:37.270 --> 06:41.059
Oh, oh, oh

06:41.110 --> 06:44.228
Maybe that was my subconscious
getting revenge on Wes.

06:44.270 --> 06:46.523
But...
what if it was more?

06:46.570 --> 06:47.640
Just to be clear,

06:47.690 --> 06:49.272
nothing actually
happened?

06:49.320 --> 06:50.355
It was just a fantasy?

06:50.410 --> 06:51.980
Right.

06:53.490 --> 06:54.651
<i>- Butwhatif
it means something?</i>

06:54.700 --> 06:56.748
I-I mean,
I had told myself

06:56.790 --> 07:00.078
that things between me and Wes
were fine after Pippa,

07:00.120 --> 07:01.622
but...

07:01.670 --> 07:02.990
maybe they're not?

07:03.040 --> 07:05.543
Or maybe you had a fantasy
about Dr. Grant

07:05.590 --> 07:07.968
because he's hot
and you have eyes.

07:08.010 --> 07:11.219
Either way,
I want it to stop.

07:11.260 --> 07:12.921
So how do I make it stop?

07:12.970 --> 07:15.007
The heart wants
what the heart wants.

07:15.060 --> 07:17.711
Well, my heart wants Wes. Good.

07:17.770 --> 07:20.011
So maybe this was just
a one-time thing,

07:20.060 --> 07:21.892
like a little blip
on the radar.

07:21.940 --> 07:23.101
Yes. Absolutely.

07:23.150 --> 07:25.357
That is exactly
what that was.

07:25.400 --> 07:26.435
It was a blip.

07:26.480 --> 07:27.527
It was less than a blip --

07:27.570 --> 07:30.107
a bloop or a bleep.

07:30.150 --> 07:32.699
Dr. Grant might've been
my one-time fantasy,

07:32.740 --> 07:34.697
but Wes is
my lifetime reality,

07:34.740 --> 07:37.323
and I am going to make
my reality fantastic.

07:37.370 --> 07:39.156
Well, that's what marriage
is all about.

07:39.200 --> 07:41.362
You know, it's easy to
fantasize about what could be,

07:41.420 --> 07:44.958
but it is hard work
to make the best of what is...

07:45.840 --> 07:46.989
What are you guys
talking about?

07:47.050 --> 07:48.506
Nothing. I got to go.

07:48.550 --> 07:49.961
Late for work.
Aiden's first day. Bye.

07:51.760 --> 07:53.831
So...

07:53.890 --> 07:55.255
what were you
talking about?

07:55.300 --> 07:56.677
Oh...
you don't want to know.

07:56.720 --> 07:57.755
Okay.

07:57.810 --> 07:58.959
But, I mean,
just to be sure,

07:59.020 --> 08:00.260
you should probably
just tell me.

08:00.310 --> 08:02.381
I promise you,
you don't want to know.

08:04.650 --> 08:07.108
But I kind of do, though.

08:07.150 --> 08:08.936
Finley:
And that is how we do it.

08:14.660 --> 08:17.618
Aah!

08:17.660 --> 08:19.901
Having a real job sucks.

08:19.950 --> 08:22.282
I can't believe people do this
every single day.

08:22.330 --> 08:25.789
But I guess that's how
the other half lives.

08:25.830 --> 08:28.299
No, this is
how everyone lives.

08:28.340 --> 08:30.251
You'll get used to it.
It just takes time.

08:30.300 --> 08:32.928
Now, if you'll excuse me,

08:32.970 --> 08:35.506
I'm gonna go home
and seduce my husband.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.466
I am not sure
why I just told you that.

08:38.510 --> 08:40.386
Sometimes my mouth starts
before I can stop.

08:44.650 --> 08:46.186
Hey. New guy.

08:46.230 --> 08:48.688
Those lattes you ruined
are coming out of your tips.

08:48.730 --> 08:50.778
Oh, you are so lucky
you're hot,

08:50.820 --> 08:51.935
or you'd be out of here.

08:54.150 --> 08:55.652
Aiden.

08:55.700 --> 08:56.906
Denise.

08:56.950 --> 08:57.940
What are you doing here?

08:57.990 --> 09:00.038
I came to get a coffee.

09:00.080 --> 09:01.570
"Cause this is
a coffee shop.

09:02.540 --> 09:04.781
So, you working here now?

09:04.830 --> 09:06.958
Yeah. It's my first day.

09:07.000 --> 09:08.582
The apron's...cute.

09:08.630 --> 09:11.122
No, it isn't.
No, it really isn't.

09:12.800 --> 09:14.757
Look, I've been meaning
to thank you.

09:14.800 --> 09:15.870
Oh, there's no need.

09:15.930 --> 09:17.580
The sex was good for me,
too.

09:18.850 --> 09:21.842
No, not for that.

09:21.890 --> 09:23.801
You know, those pills
that you sold me

09:23.850 --> 09:25.887
helped me help Bryce
win the Science Fair.

09:25.940 --> 09:27.726
You're a total lifesaver.

09:27.770 --> 09:29.306
I'm glad to be of service.

09:29.360 --> 09:30.725
Do you think maybe
you could hook me up again

09:30.770 --> 09:32.898
just because the Spelling Bee
is coming up

09:32.940 --> 09:35.238
and I just need an extra boost
to help him study?

09:35.280 --> 09:37.157
I'm sorry.

09:37.200 --> 09:39.111
I'm not really doing that
anymore.

09:39.160 --> 09:40.230
Please.

09:40.280 --> 09:41.441
I have never seen him
as happy

09:41.490 --> 09:42.946
as the day
he won the Science Fair.

09:43.000 --> 09:44.616
One last time.

09:51.250 --> 09:52.456
Guess it couldn't hurt

09:52.500 --> 09:54.753
to sell off
what's left of my stash.

09:59.220 --> 10:00.290
Hey, you.

10:00.350 --> 10:02.091
Hey yourself,

10:02.140 --> 10:03.596
How was your day?

10:03.640 --> 10:05.768
It was good.

10:05.810 --> 10:08.188
But it's about
to get better.

10:08.230 --> 10:09.265
Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh

10:09.310 --> 10:11.438
Is it raining outside?
Nope.

10:11.480 --> 10:13.107
Then why are you wearing
a raincoat?

10:13.150 --> 10:15.107
Can you please stop
asking questions.

10:15.150 --> 10:17.027
I'm sorry.
I'm just confused.

10:17.070 --> 10:18.697
Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh

10:18.740 --> 10:22.199
You got what I want,
you're not what I need

10:24.830 --> 10:28.869
Pour it over me
like gasoline

10:30.460 --> 10:33.669
Set the flame
and let it burn

10:33.710 --> 10:35.667
I don't know
what I was worried about.

10:35.710 --> 10:37.838
Wes and I were clearly
in a great place.

10:37.880 --> 10:41.384
Crazy is as crazy does,
sometimes I never learn

10:41.430 --> 10:44.502
Yeah

10:44.560 --> 10:47.177
You sure about that,
Mighty Mouse?

10:49.730 --> 10:52.392
What just happened?

10:52.440 --> 10:53.760
Nothing.

10:53.820 --> 10:54.969
Nothing.

11:02.120 --> 11:03.360
Elizabeth: Hey.

11:03.410 --> 11:05.321
Did you move
the mixing bowls?

11:05.370 --> 11:06.656
I didn't even know

11:06.700 --> 11:08.031
where they were
in the first place,

11:08.080 --> 11:10.993
so it would've been hard
for me to do that.

11:11.040 --> 11:13.839
So...you didn't do this
to our cabinets?

11:16.340 --> 11:19.082
Mom, did you rearrange
our cabinets?

11:19.130 --> 11:20.256
Oh, yeah.

11:20.300 --> 11:22.007
I couldn't sleep
last night.

11:22.050 --> 11:23.677
Organizing soothes me.

11:23.720 --> 11:26.678
So I started over here
with the spice cabinet.

11:26.720 --> 11:28.927
Everything
is color-coordinated.

11:28.980 --> 11:31.893
It goes from the spiciest
to the least spicy.

11:31.940 --> 11:33.476
I put the tastes
of the Far East

11:33.520 --> 11:34.646
all the way to the right,

11:34.690 --> 11:36.567
which is east on the map,

11:36.610 --> 11:38.851
so it makes perfect sense.

11:38.900 --> 11:40.390
No need to thank me.

11:40.450 --> 11:42.020
I'm on my way to yoga.

11:42.070 --> 11:43.367
Hatha!

11:43.410 --> 11:44.866
But I'll be back
before you know it.

11:44.910 --> 11:46.150
Namaste.

11:46.200 --> 11:47.440
Mama gotta go.

11:47.490 --> 11:48.946
Namaste, Mama got...

11:49.000 --> 11:51.207
That's a good one.

11:52.330 --> 11:54.458
Okay...

11:56.880 --> 11:58.120
She was just trying
to help.

11:58.170 --> 11:59.296
Hey.
Huh?

11:59.340 --> 12:00.796
Now that she's gone

12:00.840 --> 12:03.172
and the kids are at school,

12:03.220 --> 12:04.585
I think it's officially

12:04.640 --> 12:06.711
the first time
you and I have been alone

12:06.760 --> 12:07.807
since you got back.

