to feel wanted.

23:21.900 --> 23:25.643
Um, and we are happy

23:25.690 --> 23:28.068
that you're happy.

23:29.240 --> 23:31.026
But...

23:31.070 --> 23:33.198
the truth is,

23:33.240 --> 23:34.822
what we really need
is actually to --

23:34.870 --> 23:35.940
Oh, no, no, no, no.

23:35.990 --> 23:38.448
No, I-I know
what you need, honey.

23:38.500 --> 23:39.740
You two are so busy --

23:39.790 --> 23:41.827
barely enough time
for each other,

23:41.870 --> 23:42.996
let alone the kids.

23:43.040 --> 23:44.622
You need me to do more,

23:44.670 --> 23:45.876
and I'm happy to.

23:45.920 --> 23:47.661
I got it!

23:49.800 --> 23:51.177
I could stay here
forever.

23:53.590 --> 23:55.843
Wes: Do you guys know
where Stella is?

23:55.890 --> 23:57.176
She didn't come home

23:57.220 --> 23:58.710
after her shift
at the coffee shop,

23:58.770 --> 24:00.977
Dr. Chang says she didn't
show up at the hospital,

24:01.020 --> 24:02.647
and now she's not
answering her phone.

24:02.690 --> 24:04.010
Where is she?

24:04.060 --> 24:05.437
Wes, the last time
I talked to Stella,

24:05.480 --> 24:06.720
she was fine.

24:09.570 --> 24:10.856
Stella: Wes.

24:10.900 --> 24:11.947
Stella, where are you?

24:11.990 --> 24:13.867
Sorry I disappeared.

24:13.910 --> 24:16.698
Aiden and I
ran into some trouble.

24:16.740 --> 24:17.866
What kind of trouble?

24:17.910 --> 24:19.651
Um,
we kind of got arrested.

24:19.700 --> 24:22.112
Arrested

24:22.170 --> 24:24.457
For selling his ADD meds.

24:24.500 --> 24:25.661
I-I've been cleared
