remember the time

26:07.350 --> 26:08.897
he slept
with your boss's wife?

26:08.940 --> 26:10.510
To be fair,

26:10.560 --> 26:12.392
I mean, she did
come on pretty strong.

26:12.440 --> 26:13.851
And, Stella,
how 'bout the time

26:13.900 --> 26:15.277
you cashed in
your savings bonds for him?

26:15.320 --> 26:17.106
He used that money
to go see a therapist.

26:17.150 --> 26:19.778
He used it to buy
Minecraft upgrades.

26:19.820 --> 26:21.447
All right. I get it.

26:21.490 --> 26:24.289
No. I don't think you do.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.991
Our son is a drug dealer.

26:30.040 --> 26:32.372
We've given him
too many chances,

26:32.420 --> 26:34.297
too many
"get out of jail free" cards.

26:34.340 --> 26:36.126
If we don't draw
this line in the sand,

26:36.170 --> 26:37.797
I'm afraid
he's never gonna learn.

26:39.220 --> 26:42.008
Mom, please,
don't let him do this.

26:42.050 --> 26:43.961
I'm sorry, Stell,

26:44.020 --> 26:45.670
but I agree
with your father.

26:45.730 --> 26:48.939
I know I haven't said this
much lately, Peter,

26:48.980 --> 26:50.470
but I think you're right.

26:53.980 --> 26:56.233
I think it's time
for a little tough love.

26:56.280 --> 26:57.145
Wes.

26:58.240 --> 27:00.356
Will you talk
some sense into them?

27:02.830 --> 27:04.696
Wes?

27:04.740 --> 27:07.118
Actually, Stella,

27:07.160 --> 27:09.458
if I'm being honest,

27:09.500 --> 27:10.990
I agree with your family.

27:15.340 --> 27:20.369
You gave me strength
when I felt weak

27:20.430 --> 27:24.719
You got me out
when I dove too deep

27:24.760 --> 27:26.216
"The world is yours"
you said

27:26.270 --> 27:27.760
Hey.

27:27.810 --> 27:29.687
Hey.

27:29.730 --> 27:31.346
Where's Mom and Dad?

27:31.400 --> 27:34.062
I love you so,
I love you so

27:34.110 --> 27:35.930
I love you so
Dad says that

27:35.980 --> 27:37.732
you're on your own
this time.

27:37.780 --> 27:41.819
Wow, that is just great.

27:41.860 --> 27:43.817
I can't believe
I actually thought

27:43.870 --> 27:46.111
things might be different
between us now,

27:46.160 --> 27:48.492
but I guess people
never change.

27:48.540 --> 27:50.781
Kind of ironic coming from
a guy sitting in jail

27:50.830 --> 27:52.878
who promised me
he'd turn his life around.

27:52.920 --> 27:54.331
Now you sound like Dad.

27:54.380 --> 27:55.415
Good.

27:57.630 --> 28:00.088
Because he's really worried
about you.

28:00.130 --> 28:01.256
We all are.

28:01.300 --> 28:03.257
Aiden, this is serious.

28:03.300 --> 28:05.041
You think
I don't know that?

28:05.100 --> 28:06.499
Well, it's hard to tell
sometimes.

28:06.560 --> 28:07.880
Everything
is a joke to you.

28:07.930 --> 28:09.762
You have no idea
what you're talking about,

28:09.810 --> 28:11.630
because you have no idea
who I really am.

28:11.690 --> 28:13.931
Then tell me.
What's the point?

28:13.980 --> 28:15.857
Everyone decided
I was a screw-up

28:15.900 --> 28:17.686
a long time ago.

28:17.730 --> 28:19.528
I'm done trying to prove
everyone wrong.

28:19.570 --> 28:21.607
Prove us wrong?

28:21.650 --> 28:23.903
How is selling drugs
proving us wrong?

28:23.950 --> 28:25.770
How is wrecking
Lizzie's car

28:25.830 --> 28:27.821
to impress a bunch of
sorority girls proving us wrong?

28:27.870 --> 28:29.827
And how was
getting me arrested --

28:29.870 --> 28:31.861
how was that
proving us wrong?

28:31.910 --> 28:34.322
Arms as strong
as the wind

28:34.380 --> 28:35.666
The truth is

28:35.710 --> 28:37.872
all you've ever cared about
is yourself,

28:37.920 --> 28:39.627
Dressed ready to Kill

28:39.670 --> 28:41.468
Stella, why do you think
I got those stupid pills

28:41.510 --> 28:43.421
in the first place?

28:43.470 --> 28:47.293
Head in the clouds
but feet on the ground

28:47.350 --> 28:49.057
With you

28:49.100 --> 28:52.479
It's all safe and sound

28:52.520 --> 28:54.056
Hush, hush, baby
Registrar's office says that,

28:54.100 --> 28:56.478
if you don't get your grades up
by the end of semester,

28:56.520 --> 28:57.817
they're pulling
your work-study.

28:57.860 --> 29:00.101
They can't do that.

29:00.150 --> 29:01.561
I need this job.

29:01.610 --> 29:02.896
Well,
if you need this job so bad,

29:02.950 --> 29:04.315
then maybe you should --
I don't know --

29:04.360 --> 29:05.566
start doing it?

29:05.610 --> 29:08.113
And nobody
will break you

29:08.160 --> 29:10.652
Whoa.
Where'd you get those?

29:10.700 --> 29:14.534
My doc wrote me a prescription
a couple weeks ago.

29:14.580 --> 29:15.741
Ever since
Stella got sick,

29:15.790 --> 29:18.999
I've been having trouble
focusing.

29:19.040 --> 29:20.917
A smile filled with life

29:20.960 --> 29:22.416
Between school, work,

29:22.470 --> 29:24.006
driving back and forth
to see her,

29:24.050 --> 29:26.542
I'm exhausted.

29:26.590 --> 29:29.673
Last week, I fell asleep
driving my sister's car

29:29.720 --> 29:31.427
and totaled it.

29:31.470 --> 29:33.222
Dude,
I'm glad you're okay.

29:33.270 --> 29:36.262
Hush, hush, baby

29:36.310 --> 29:37.857
And nobody will break you

29:37.900 --> 29:42.394
I'm sorry to just
unload on you, but...

29:42.440 --> 29:45.694
it's so hard
to be here doing this

29:45.740 --> 29:48.903
when my whole body
feels like

29:48.950 --> 29:50.770
I should be there
with her.

29:50.830 --> 29:52.696
Mm, mm-mm, mm-mm

29:52.750 --> 29:55.788
I mean, what if --

29:55.830 --> 29:57.787
What if I'm not there.

29:59.540 --> 30:01.918
You know, if you want to
spend more time with your sister,

30:01.960 --> 30:05.965
then maybe
you don't need this job.

30:06.010 --> 30:08.638
You can make a lot more money
selling those things.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.386
Stella: That's why you
started selling drugs?

30:14.680 --> 30:15.841
Why didn't you
tell Mom and Dad

30:15.890 --> 30:17.187
the truth
about Lizzie's car?

30:17.230 --> 30:19.141
Because they had enough
to worry about.

30:19.190 --> 30:21.261
I didn't want them
to worry about me.

30:21.320 --> 30:25.735
So this is my fault...

30:25.780 --> 30:27.020
again.

30:27.070 --> 30:29.448
That's not
what I'm saying.

30:29.490 --> 30:30.946
I'm not blaming you.

30:30.990 --> 30:33.539
I'm trying to get you
to understand me.

30:33.580 --> 30:35.571
I didn't mean
to become this guy,

30:35.620 --> 30:38.419
and I wasn't trying
to take the easy way out.

30:38.460 --> 30:39.950
I was trying
to make it all work,

30:40.000 --> 30:41.661
and it just happened.

30:47.510 --> 30:52.095
I don't want to be this guy
anymore, Stella.

30:52.140 --> 30:53.756
But I don't know
what to do.

30:56.850 --> 30:59.649
Aiden,
it's gonna be okay.

30:59.690 --> 31:01.852
If they won't get you
out of here, I will.

31:01.900 --> 31:04.278
Where are you gonna
get the money?

31:04.320 --> 31:06.061
I'll figure it out.

31:06.110 --> 31:08.272
I promise.

31:08.320 --> 31:10.527
Elizabeth: Hey.

31:10.570 --> 31:12.447
Hey. How you doin'?

31:12.490 --> 31:15.573
Oh, I'm fine.

31:15.620 --> 31:18.032
My mom,
on the other hand...

31:18.080 --> 31:21.710
um, between the breakup
and everything with Aiden,

31:21.750 --> 31:22.956
she's not doing great.

31:26.210 --> 31:28.042
I just don't think
this is the time to tell her

31:28.090 --> 31:29.421
we're not happy
having her here.

31:31.180 --> 31:32.329
Right.

31:32.390 --> 31:33.425
We'll make it work.

31:33.470 --> 31:34.676
Yeah.

31:34.720 --> 31:38.133
Sure, we'll have to suffer
a little bit.

31:38.180 --> 31:41.434
That's what you do
for family.

31:46.730 --> 31:47.856
Diego: Love you.

31:50.990 --> 31:53.368
Oh, man, I've wanted one of
these fancy European scooters

31:53.410 --> 31:54.650
since I was old enough
to drive!

31:54.700 --> 31:56.577
Thank you!
Ride it in good health.

32:04.340 --> 32:05.705
What's got Nurse Gretchen
so excited?

32:08.010 --> 32:09.796
Nurse Gretchen: Whee!

32:09.840 --> 32:11.831
Eat, pray, love, bitches!

32:11.880 --> 32:13.006
Did you sell
your scooter?

32:14.090 --> 32:15.922
Why?
I thought you loved that thing.

32:15.970 --> 32:18.428
Mm.
I love my brother more.

32:18.470 --> 32:21.633
I needed the money
to bail him out of jail.

32:21.690 --> 32:24.352
He got arrested
for selling drugs,

32:24.400 --> 32:26.858
and no one in my family
will help bail him out.

32:26.900 --> 32:28.777
I mean,
what is wrong with him?

32:28.820 --> 32:31.027
And when did they become a
chorus to a bad country song?

32:32.820 --> 32:34.367
Nothing's wrong with him.

32:34.410 --> 32:36.026
This is what happens
to families

32:36.080 --> 32:37.696
when someone gets cancer.

32:37.740 --> 32:38.901
With my brother,

32:38.950 --> 32:40.327
same thing happened
to my family.

32:40.370 --> 32:41.952
You know, my parents
never filled the void

32:42.000 --> 32:44.537
that Jesse left.

32:44.580 --> 32:46.491
Look, Stella,
you have to realize that

32:46.540 --> 32:48.702
when you got sick,
so did they.

32:48.750 --> 32:51.754
What happened to them,
what they went through --

32:51.800 --> 32:54.258
Think about the fear
that they had of losing you.

32:54.300 --> 32:56.678
You know, it just --
it doesn't go away overnight.

32:59.180 --> 33:00.966
I got to go get
my brother...

33:01.020 --> 33:02.476
Hey,
you just sold your scooter.

33:02.520 --> 33:04.397
Let me give you a ride.
No, no, I'll take a cab.

33:04.440 --> 33:05.896
I'm driving right
by there. It's fine.

33:05.940 --> 33:07.601
I can take care of myself,

33:07.650 --> 33:09.641
I know you can.

33:09.690 --> 33:11.237
I'm not trying
to take care of you.

33:11.280 --> 33:13.146
I'm just
trying to give you a ride.

33:13.200 --> 33:14.270
Well, you can't.

33:18.870 --> 33:21.862
You have to stop
offering me rides

33:21.910 --> 33:25.244
and...amazing advice

33:25.290 --> 33:26.451
and making me feel like

33:26.500 --> 33:27.877
you're the only person
on Earth

33:27.920 --> 33:30.491
who really gets me.

33:30.550 --> 33:32.587
I didn't...

33:32.630 --> 33:34.086
I didn't know
I was doing that.

33:34.130 --> 33:36.588
Well, you are.

33:36.640 --> 33:38.597
And it's really
got to stop.

33:38.640 --> 33:40.677
Because I'm married
to an incredible man

33:40.720 --> 33:42.427
who I love
with all of my heart,

33:42.470 --> 33:45.269
and it...
really sucks to know

33:45.310 --> 33:46.937
that no matter
how hard he tries,

33:46.980 --> 33:49.563
he might never understand
what I'm going through

33:49.610 --> 33:50.725
the way that you do.

34:03.410 --> 34:05.401
Well,
this is worse than jail.

34:11.630 --> 34:19.630
[ Billy Raffoul's
"Dark Four Door" plays ]

34:20.850 --> 34:23.467
You got up

34:23.520 --> 34:25.386
You felt you should

34:28.850 --> 34:30.806
I keep trying
to tell myself

34:30.860 --> 34:33.351
I woulda done the same
had I could

34:33.400 --> 34:35.687
Thank you
for bailing out Aiden.

34:35.739 --> 34:38.812
Well, I wanted you to know
I got your back.

34:38.860 --> 34:40.065
Because we're married.

34:40.120 --> 34:41.610
I never thought
that you would

34:41.659 --> 34:42.946
Not that you'd know it
from what I just heard.

34:42.989 --> 34:44.150
Wes.

34:44.199 --> 34:45.860
It's not like that.
Really?

34:45.909 --> 34:47.650
Because it sounded like

34:47.710 --> 34:48.949
you were telling
another man

34:49.000 --> 34:50.741
that he's the only one

34:50.790 --> 34:52.621
that really
understands you.

34:52.670 --> 34:55.002
I'm sorry.

34:55.050 --> 34:57.542
I-I wasn't trying
'to hurt you.

34:57.590 --> 35:00.332
So long
as you come back home

35:00.390 --> 35:01.880
So I went south
to define me

35:01.930 --> 35:04.718
So, is Dr. Handsome

35:04.770 --> 35:07.478
the reason you've been
acting so weird?

35:07.520 --> 35:10.399
Until then I'm still
looking for you

35:10.440 --> 35:11.646
Yes.

35:11.690 --> 35:12.725
In every dark
four door

35:12.770 --> 35:14.147
Do you have feelings
for him?

35:14.190 --> 35:17.820
I have a connection
with him.

35:17.860 --> 35:21.023
But it's nothing like
the one that I have with you.

35:21.070 --> 35:23.198
I'm in love with you.

35:23.240 --> 35:24.651
You are the love of my life,

35:24.700 --> 35:28.910
and -- and he's just a friend...
who gets me.

35:28.960 --> 35:31.452
I don't sleep enough
at night

35:31.500 --> 35:37.371
Wes, you're my husband
and my soul mate.

35:37.420 --> 35:38.797
And he's a great guy,

35:38.840 --> 35:40.467
but he'll never make me feel
the way that you do.

35:40.510 --> 35:43.138
You sure about that?
Yes.

35:43.180 --> 35:44.966
I want to be with you.

35:45.010 --> 35:46.387
I choose you.

35:46.430 --> 35:47.591
As long as
you come back home

35:47.640 --> 35:49.130
And I choose us.
I always will.

35:49.180 --> 35:51.729
So I went south
to define me

35:51.770 --> 35:53.226
And someday
you'll find me

35:53.270 --> 35:55.102
Please say something.

35:55.150 --> 35:57.642
What do you want me
to say?

35:57.690 --> 35:59.101
The truth.

35:59.150 --> 36:00.697
Until then I'm still
looking for you

36:00.740 --> 36:02.276
In every dark four door

36:02.320 --> 36:05.119
The truth is...

36:05.160 --> 36:06.821
Until then
I'm still looking for you

36:06.870 --> 36:08.747
...]I don't choose you,
Stella.

36:08.790 --> 36:10.861
In every dark four door

36:10.910 --> 36:13.629
The way I feel about you
is not a choice for me

36:13.670 --> 36:16.913
any more than it is
a choice to breathe.

36:16.960 --> 36:19.964
So knowing that
I'm a choice to you,

36:20.010 --> 36:21.876
one of many options,
it's -- it...

36:23.300 --> 36:25.098
Honestly, there aren't words
to describe

36:25.140 --> 36:26.676
how that makes me feel.

36:26.720 --> 36:29.212
Until then I'm still
looking for you

36:29.270 --> 36:31.762
In every dark four door

36:31.810 --> 36:33.642
I need some time
to think.

36:33.690 --> 36:35.351
Wes,
that's not what I meant.

36:35.400 --> 36:37.266
Until then I'm still
looking for you

36:37.320 --> 36:40.483
In every dark four door

36:43.530 --> 36:44.861
Mom.

36:44.910 --> 36:46.116
Ida: Hmm?

36:46.160 --> 36:47.275
What's all this?

36:47.330 --> 36:48.820
Nothing.

36:48.870 --> 36:50.076
I just ordered delivery

36:50.120 --> 36:51.952
from that Moroccan place
you like.

36:52.000 --> 36:53.911
I thought you could use
a little date night --

36:53.960 --> 36:55.780
the two of you.

36:55.830 --> 36:57.662
And the kids
are all tucked in.

36:59.670 --> 37:01.798
You didn't have
to do that.

37:01.840 --> 37:03.717
Yes, I did.

37:03.760 --> 37:07.298
You guys have been so sweet
to have me here.

37:07.350 --> 37:08.749
But I've been
a little tone-deaf.

37:08.810 --> 37:11.131
So from now on,

37:11.180 --> 37:13.262
I will be
as quiet as a mouse.

37:13.310 --> 37:14.892
You won't even know
I'm here.

37:14.940 --> 37:17.557
You heard us talking,
didn't you?

37:17.610 --> 37:18.566
Every word.

37:18.610 --> 37:20.317
But you were right.

37:20.360 --> 37:22.237
I didn't mean to be such
an imposition.

37:22.280 --> 37:27.946
It's just
without Poppy or your father...

37:27.990 --> 37:30.288
I don't really have anyone
to talk to.

37:31.750 --> 37:33.616
Well, that's not true.

37:33.660 --> 37:36.960
Okay, you --
you have us.

37:37.000 --> 37:39.742
And this is
where you belong.

37:39.800 --> 37:41.336
Oh, honey,
no, it's not.

37:41.380 --> 37:44.008
Yes, it is.

37:44.050 --> 37:46.212
You're my mother.

37:46.260 --> 37:48.297
And you're staying,
okay?

37:48.350 --> 37:50.637
We insist.
Yeah.

37:50.680 --> 37:52.591
Are you sure?
Yes!

37:52.640 --> 37:54.847
Come on,
who's gonna spoil our kids

37:54.890 --> 37:57.052
and move our stuff
to ridiculous places?

37:58.270 --> 38:00.102
The -- The spice cabinet
makes sense.

38:00.150 --> 38:01.561
I stand by that, guys.

38:01.610 --> 38:07.026
Uh, what do you say
that tonight

38:07.070 --> 38:10.370
we all have dinner
together?

38:10.410 --> 38:13.368
I'd really like that.

38:13.410 --> 38:14.650
Oh, guess what,

38:14.710 --> 38:16.246
the lamb meatballs
are to die for!

38:16.290 --> 38:19.328
- You are
going to love them!

38:21.000 --> 38:23.503
When it comes
to the people you love most,

38:23.550 --> 38:25.166
you have to be there
for them,

38:25.220 --> 38:26.540
even when it's hard.

38:26.590 --> 38:28.752
Taunted by that
new daylight

38:28.800 --> 38:30.711
Aiden.

38:30.760 --> 38:32.421
When you just can't sleep
before the morn

38:32.470 --> 38:34.552
Peter: How'd you get out
of jail? Wes bailed me out.

38:34.600 --> 38:38.264
<i>Nice to know someone
still gives a damn about me.</i>

38:38.310 --> 38:41.473
I do give a damn
about you.

38:41.520 --> 38:43.773
You think
this is easy for me?

38:43.820 --> 38:45.356
Seems pretty easy.

38:45.400 --> 38:46.856
Well, it's not.

38:46.900 --> 38:49.278
You ain't nobody's
little girl

38:49.320 --> 38:51.368
Son.

38:51.410 --> 38:52.650
You ain't nobody's
sacred son

38:52.700 --> 38:54.156
I'm sorry.

38:54.200 --> 38:55.998
But I'm worried about you.

38:56.040 --> 38:58.998
You can't keep going down
the path you're on.

38:59.040 --> 39:00.417
You needed a wake-up call,

39:00.460 --> 39:02.030
and I thought
a few nights in jail

39:02.090 --> 39:03.205
might be exactly that.

39:03.250 --> 39:04.797
It's not that simple,
Dad.

39:04.840 --> 39:07.548
I'll be comin' home

39:07.590 --> 39:09.888
So you don't
have to be alone

39:09.930 --> 39:11.295
Remember that time

39:11.340 --> 39:13.058
I went backpacking
up North?

39:13.100 --> 39:17.389
I kind of got arrested

39:17.430 --> 39:19.182
for "borrowing" an ATV
from a campsite.

39:19.230 --> 39:21.016
Well, I'm ragged, too,
just like you

39:21.060 --> 39:23.142
Suspended sentence.

39:23.190 --> 39:26.023
I...paid a fine,

39:26.070 --> 39:33.079
but apparently the conviction
is still on my record.

39:33.120 --> 39:38.286
Feelin' like
a little child

39:38.330 --> 39:44.793
Aiden, I'm so sorry.

39:44.840 --> 39:46.205
I didn't know.

39:46.250 --> 39:47.911
It gets worse.

39:47.960 --> 39:53.342
Those pills I was selling --
Schedule II drug.

39:53.390 --> 39:56.963
Same as cocaine,

39:57.020 --> 39:58.135
which means...

39:58.180 --> 39:59.807
You're facing
a felony charge.

39:59.850 --> 40:01.386
Lately,
I've been thinkin' of

40:01.440 --> 40:03.511
Yeah.

40:03.560 --> 40:04.971
All the losing
that I've done in love

40:05.020 --> 40:07.102
What am I gonna do, Dad?

40:07.150 --> 40:09.858
I don't know, son.

40:09.900 --> 40:14.360
The wind,
she steals my sweet caress

40:14.410 --> 40:16.196
- Please feel me
IN your emptiness

40:16.240 --> 40:18.322
You have to keep trying,

40:18.370 --> 40:19.952
even when things
